<font size="2"><b>Assassin</b></font> - <font size="1">7/18/2002 at 09:28 PM</font>
<p>I like Tabber, he has several times dropped what he was doing and was at a place where I needed help 20 minutes before everyone else.<br />
<br />
As for Jehm, I like him, he's funny, but I don't know about that.<br />
<br />
I have to say that I am not all over this whole "class officers" things. When I need help as a Shaman, I know bustyn will do what she can to help me. If I need help as a monk, I know kaedo will give superb advice.<br />
<br />
Also, I even more strongly disagree with officer tags for class officers. I'd rather not have 18 officers in this guild, to be quite honest. Whether or not they have power over anything. An officer tag is easily abused.<br />
<br />
In addition to that, it causes confusion in authority among those outside the guild. When I get into a sticky situation with a guild outside mine, I /guildstatus them, find the officer, if any, and talk to them. I can easily see how an Class Officer will try to step in and be the problem solver, and quite possibly make things worse.<br />
<br />
But if we are going to do the Class Officer thing anyway, we could just call them the officers, give them the title of officer on boards, and refer everyone to them.<br />
<br />
I'm not trying to pick a fight or anything, I could be wrong, or my thoughts may be irrevelant, but just thought I should mention it.<br />
<br />
Now, for Tabber as a normal officer, I dont think I have any problems with that, he has shown many times his loyalty to the guild and determination to help them. I have heard of his /tells to other members talking of how unfair our loot decisions are sometimes, but I believe after a few weeks in officer chat, he will understand things better and become a better leader.<br />
<br />
I think that's all I have to say hehe.</p>

