<font size="2"><b>Kaedo</b></font> - <font size="1">7/19/2002 at 07:25 AM</font>
<p>Like every member in MV was an officer, eventually =b.  Silly but true.  I think the absolute power of an officer should not be taken lightly.  We really need an alternative way to appreciate those members that are truly dedicated to the guild.<br />
<br />
With that said, you mentioned they would really only be figure-head "officers."  I personally don't have a problem with that, until someone abuses their power.  I would only ask you make it very clear that there will be consequences for abusing their officer powers.<br />
<br />
Otherwise, I am ALL FOR delegating some responsibilty out.  Bem you shoulder way too much, we really need to work together as leaders and spread the load out a bit.<br />
<br />
As far as Tabber as a full officer... I am only concerned that a change may disrupt the continuity? that we currently share.  Maybe I am reading too far into what little I have read or heard from Tabber.  But I am not sure he would "fit in" so to speak.  I just figure that all the officers we currently have are pretty close friends, and outside of raid chatter, I don't know Tabber from Adam.</p>
